target/
.git/
.idea/
.vscode/
**/target/
**/*.log
**/.DS_Store
infra/
docs/
test-harness/
# Stale Next.js build artefacts must not bleed into the docker context — the
# in-container `npm run build` re-generates these. If we ship a local out/
# alongside the container build, Next.js may keep BOTH old and new page chunks
# (route index.html ends up referencing the stale chunk → "Edit URL invisible"
# bug). Force a clean rebuild every time.
apps/*/.next/
apps/*/out/
apps/*/node_modules/
